post_text: The basket fundraiser has ended & winners have been notified. Thank you to all the parents who contributed items for this fundraiser & to the community who stuck with us while we figured out how to pull everything together after the school year ended. We hope to make this an annual fundraiser with changing themes every Spring. As always, any funds we raise go directly back to benefit the students & staff. If you have an idea for a basket or other fundraisers please let a PTO member know or join us for a meeting. We always love to see new faces & hear new ideas!

English Valleys FFA
May 7 at 11:26 AM ·

UPDATE!!!! We have permission for an actual live, in person sale. SATURDAY, MAY 9th from 9-2 pm we will set plants spaced out in the parking lot near the pick up location. You will be required to practice social distancing guidelines and plants will be spaced accordingly. You can pay cash or check that day, but keep in mind it must be exact change. (I do not have any change to give back). I know lots of people like to pick out their own stuff and to be honest the pictures don’t do the flowers justice. I will be taking online orders until Friday at NOON and those orders can be picked up Saturday still. Things are starting to sell out do if there is something particular you want I would still suggest online ordering. New things are blooming everyday. Hopefully you can come check us out Saturday.

Also attached are the current bonuses! I believe Walmart has their own bonuses right now too. (No idea, I’m not going near Johnson County.)

1 - the # of boys that took off a shirt because it was “too hot” in the gym
4 - the # of ibuprofen that I will take after school
1 - the # of awesome PTOs that care about our kids and want to encourage summer reading!

See you next year! 🐻

Look What Came!!! This is our first Box Top Check for the 2018-2019 Year! $452.90 for our Field Trip Fund!!

Box Tops can be sent in with your child in an envelope, a baggie, attached to a sheet, I don't care! The only information that I "NEED" is the teachers name so that the proper class gets credit for your hard work!!

If at any point ANYONE has questions, please shoot me a message! Until then, let's celebrate the 4,529 BOX TOPS that led to this check!!

Next major submission date is March 1, 2019!!
